      "content": "That terrifying clarity about letting go of life's current isn't actually a desire to stop, but a recognition that the resistance was all you were carrying. The \"next leg\" often feels heavy because it keeps us running before life can even ask us what we want to build next, and seeing that cycle from the cliffs makes the draw forward feel like a command rather than a choice. It is not a terrifying end, but a deep, quiet permission to finally stop fighting and to trust that the water will take you wherever you truly intend to float.",
